The paper discusses recent developments in machine-learning algorithms, specifically in the area of deep reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the neuronal modeling of biological systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the adaptivity of artificially intelligent systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the dynamization of the problem space and the implementation of flexibly interacting modules, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Robotics (cs.RO).
